results.name: Odd numbers that have middle divisors.
comment: Odd numbers k such that the symmetric representation of sigma(k) has an odd number of parts.
For the definition of middle divisors, see A067742.
Let t be a term of A005408. Then t is in this sequence iff A067742(t) != 0. (End)
example: 9 is in the sequence because it's an odd number and the symmetric representation of sigma(9) = 13 has an odd number of parts (more exactly three parts), as shown below:
